[[=]]
+++ The Presidential Instant Pudding
[[/=]]
[[collapsible show="+ Open Recipe" hide="by Alex Thorley"]]



Hey everyone, Alex Thorley here with my 



People are always talking about this "meal prep" thing so I figured I would try it out myself and "prep" some pudding. That s where the proof is, as they say ha hehe ha. 

[[image https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/1/12/Packet%2C_food_product_%28AM_2015.4.46-1%29.jpg]]


Anyway, on to the ingredients:

[[div class="quote"]]
* 1 cup (200 g) granulated sugar
* ¾ cup (96 g) cornstarch
* ¾ cup (96 g) nonfat dry milk powder
* 1 teaspoon kosher salt
* 2 whole vanilla beans
[[/div]]

[[image https://scp-sandbox-3.wdfiles.com/local--files/fragment%3Aartexchange2023listpages4/dry%20pudding]]

Instructions:

[[div class="quote"]]
# Whisk sugar, cornstarch, milk powder, and salt;
# Add vanilla bean seeds, whisk. Cut vanilla bean pods. 
# Place pods in jar, whisk. Add mixture to jar, whisk. Store in a cool, dry place, whisk.
[[/div]]

[[image flickr:13922224163]]

For wet pudding:
[[div class="quote"]]
Add 2 cups of milk to ½ cup of mix over high heat, whisking constantly. Bring to a boil, whisk, reduce heat and continue whisking until the mixt coats the back of the whisk (about 3 to 5 minutes). Let refractor for at least 5 minutes.
[[/div]]

[[image https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/7/7c/Jackfruit_pudding.jpg]]
Don't forget to eat the pudding!
